Emoni's job within the Imperial Secret Agency mainly
involved seduction. The goal was to recruit as many
collaborators as possible to maintain Queen Caron's regime.
Many of the methods used involved utilizing Emoni's
beautiful body.

Emoni served two completely different women. The great
widow, who guided her, was the adventurer guild leader. The
queen Caron, who ruled the empire and tried to use her.

Good and evil, normal and abnormal, independence and
dependence... In every aspect, the two are polar opposites,
and Emoni understood that she could never truly respect
Queen Caron for her entire life.

Emoni was already in a place where she couldn't turn back.
And she could hear voices, saying that she was reckless and
foolish. That's why she couldn't turn back, but she also
couldn't move forward.

Emoni found it much easier to live as a secret agent.
However, her inherent goodness and the interference of the
great widow hindered her. Vanity and the desire for approval
kept Emoni in the shadows, making her feel like an
inadequate member of the secret agency.

Emoni often recalls the words of the great widow, who said
that everyone has the wings of freedom.

And then, she realized. Her own wings were wounded and
dirty, unable to fly anymore.
